1) Core Insight

Systems don’t just limit outcomes—they shape how problems are represented.
Changing the representation often changes what’s possible.

⸻

2) What looks like a “jailbreak” (neutral definition)

What people call a “jailbreak” is usually:

* reframing the task
* shifting abstraction level
* changing constraints
* or altering interface expectations

Not “breaking the system”—just operating in a different coordinate frame.

⸻

3) Underlying Mechanisms

A. Reframing

Same problem, different lens → different solution space

B. Abstraction Shift

Zoom in/out → new degrees of freedom

C. Constraint Translation

Turn hard constraints into soft or orthogonal ones

D. Representation Change

Text → story → metaphor → structure → code

⸻

4) System Model

Problem (constrained)
        ↓
Identify constraint type
        ↓
Apply operator:
    - Reframe
    - Abstract
    - Translate
    - Represent
        ↓
New problem surface
        ↓
Solve within new space

⸻

